= 1928 Begins

January arrives cold and crisp in Berlin. The Republic enters its tenth year.

The newspapers report the usual concerns: reparations, unemployment, political squabbles in the Reichstag. President Hindenburg continues his quiet stewardship. Foreign Minister Stresemann prepares for another round of negotiations.

The SPD begins the year with the challenges ahead: maintaining coalition stability, addressing worker concerns, defending democracy against its critics.

The work continues. Continues...

